  • Method Details

    • get

      V get(K key)
      Method that returns the value that is mapped to a given key. If the key is not present in the map, the method returns null
      Parameters:
      key - Given key to look for in map
      Returns:
      The value associated to the given key

    • put

      void put(K key, V value)
      Method that inserts a given value into the map while being associated to a given key.
      Parameters:
      key - Given key to store in map
      value - Given value to associate with a given key in map

    • remove

      V remove(K key)
      Method that removes a value that is associated to a given key. The method returns null if the key is not present in the map.
      Parameters:
      key - Given key to remove the value associated to it.
      Returns:
      The value removed, null if the key is not present in the map.

      Parameters:

      Returns:
      True if the key is present in the map, false otherwise.
